<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09120f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09120f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09120f"> 120(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pleasing intelligence</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The bishop of Antioch]</font> was sent in chains to Rome as a public spectacle; and when he arrived at Troas he received the <mark>pleasing intelligence</mark> that the persecution of Antioch was already at an end. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) II, 245n (Chapter XVI)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
